HEADWORD: Euterpe
<hw>Eu*ter"pe</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <?/, fr. <?/
delightful; <grk>e'y^</grk> well + <?/ to delight.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Class. Myth.)</fld> <def>The Muse who presided over
music.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of palms, some species of
which are elegant trees.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Euterpean</ent>⟦br⟧
